    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix inconsistent polar decoder tree construction causing power control errors\n\n### Summary\nThe `add_nodes` function in the polar decoder was creating an inconsistent tree structure where the right subtree was not always properly initialized when `all_frozen_below==0`. This led to downstream decoding functions accessing uninitialized pointers, causing incorrect transmit power levels.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrPolar_tools/nr_polar_decoding_tools.c`: Consolidated left and right subtree creation logic in `add_nodes` function to ensure both are created together when needed.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain RNTI values and aggregation levels, the gNB would calculate incorrect transmit power levels for UEs, causing UEs to transmit at wrong power levels. This was observable as UEs either not being able to establish connections or having poor throughput due to power mismatch.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable with DCI formats where the polar decoder tree construction would result in an inconsistent structure, leading to incorrect LLR calculations and ultimately wrong power control commands being sent to UEs.\n"
}